We managed to get hold of his consultant who, very kindly, has been trying so hard to get hold of any doctor/registrar at the hospital to she’s some light on his case and help with the plan, but “it’s the weekend, no doctors work on the weekend” is what we have been told!

When I finally got in, I stopped the nurse from unplugging him completely from all machines “to transfer him to a room as this was policy”. This would have killed my dad in 2 mins. I’m so angry and frustrated my dad deteriorated as a result of these poor decisions

As the doctor stayed with me to convince me to go home, a nurse - following orders - took my dad off his breathing machine as “the numbers were too high” not knowing they are high because he depends on them to stay alive

I can’t stop wondering why hospitals are not given points of contacts for specialist hospitals/staff specialising in various critical illnesses so all decisions are based on facts not hunches! Had I not insisted I stay he would have died in their care due to the lack of knowledge

My dad is in hospital. Whilst the staff have been lovely & working hard to save him, they have no idea about his terminal illness. COVID meant that they wanted us to leave immediately after he arrived but that resulted in so many uninformed decisions that made his condition worse
